Meaning of Official Certification

In this license, “official certification” means certification, accreditation, approval, or authorization issued by the SAIL authors, a regulator, a standards body, a government authority, or another external institution.

This restriction does not prevent truthful description of deterministic structural certificates, conformance results, behavioral validation results, mutation-detection results, audit results, or realization certificates generated by a SAIL implementation.

Such generated artifacts must not be represented as regulatory, legal, financial, medical, safety-critical, governmental, or institutional certification unless separately issued by an authorized body.

